The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Friday, April 09, 2004 				 Cop strategy for antiques
 A STAFF REPORTER																								The repeated thefts and burglaries in museums and temples have driven the city police to adopt measures to protect the antiques kept in Calcuttas museums.																								A high-level meeting was convened at Lalbazar on Thursday to adopt the strategy. Senior officers met the authorities of Mahabodhi Society, Victoria Memorial, Indian Museum, Bangiya Sahitya Parishad, Asutosh Museum, Marble Palace, Gandhi Museum and Asiatic Society.																								The museum authorities were advised to instal modern equipment and gadgets, like sensor alarms and closed-circuit television to protect the antiques, apart from maintaining a detailed catalogue of the items and conducting a vigil while opening and closing the museum.
